<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-08T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-08T04:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">761.71/171: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-08T12:00:00+03:00">January 8,
                                    1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 8—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>36. I have learned from a source which I regard as reliable that the
                            railroad between Lwow and Przemysl has been cleared and ordered <pb facs="0465" n="453" xml:id="pg_453"/> to be kept cleared for the
                            next [few?] days. The same informant advised me that whereas until
                            recently Rumanian forces had been withdrawn from Bessarabia they have
                            now entered the southern half of that district and are engaged in
                            fortifying it—although the main Rumanian defense line is still on the
                            Prut and Danube Rivers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>